    4  -rw-         796    <no date>  vlan.dat 				- AUTOMATIC SAVED BY VLAN


*** VTP UPDATE - INCLUDES INFORMATION FROM SH VTP STATUS AND THE VLAN.DAT


VTP MODES
===========
1. SERVER Mode
	- DEFAULT VTP MODE
	- CAN ADD,EDIT & DELETE VLANS
	- IF RECEIVES A VTP UPDATE W/ A HIGHER REVISION#, IT WILL OVERWRITE VLAN.DAT AND FORWARD THAT VTP UPDATE OUT ON ALL TRUNKS

	
2. CLIENT Mode
	- NO ADD, NO EDIT, NO DELETE VLANS
	- IF RECEIVES A VTP UPDATE W/ A HIGHER REVISION#, IT WILL OVERWRITE VLAN.DAT AND FORWARD THAT VTP UPDATE OUT ON ALL TRUNKS

3. TRANSPARENT Mode
	- CAN ADD, EDIT & DELETE VLANS
	- IF THERE IS A VLAN CHANGE, IT WILL NOT INCREMENT REV#, IT WIL NOT FORWARD A VTP UPDATE.
	- CONFIGURATION REV# IS ALWAYS ZERO, *IF RECEIVES A VTP UPDATE: WILL NOT PROCESS, BUT WILL FORWARD THE UPDATE ON ALL TRUNKS.
	

BEST PRACTICE WHEN THERE IS A NEW SWITCHES 
-------------------------------------------
1. CHECK VLAN.DAT, USE THIS COMMAND
	delete flash:vlan.dat

2. ALWAYS CONFIGURE THE NEW SWITCH WITH VTP DOMAIN AND VTP PASSWORD


! use command #sho vtp status


VTP CONIGURATION
===================

WAYS TO CONFIGURE VTP
1. VTP CONFIG MODE WAY
	- SUPPORTED BY NEWER CISCO SWITCHES
	- INCLUDED IN CCNA EXAM
	- SYNTAX:
		conf t
		! IF YOU WANT THE SWITCH TO BECOME A VTP SERVER
		vtp mode server  
		!
		! IF YOU WANT THE SWITCH TO BECOME A VTP CLIENT
		vtp mode client
		!
		! IF YOU WANT THE SWITCH TO BECOME A VTP TRANSPARENT
		vtp mode transparent
		!
		vtp version 2
		vtp domain <domain name>
		vtp domain password <password>
		exit
		!
		conf t
		vtp mode server  
		vtp mode client/server/transparent
		vtp version 2
		vtp domain <domain name>
		vtp domain password <password>
		exit



2. VTP Database MODE WAY
	- SUPPORTED BY OLDER SWITCHES
	- SYNTAX:	
		enable
		vlan database
		! IF YOU WANT THE SWITCH TO BECOME A VTP SERVER
		vtp server  
		!
		! IF YOU WANT THE SWITCH TO BECOME A VTP CLIENT
		vtp client
		!
		! IF YOU WANT THE SWITCH TO BECOME A VTP TRANSPARENT
		vtp transparent
		!
		vtp version 2
		vtp domain <domain name>
		vtp password <password>
		exit


